00:45:52.200 --> 00:45:53.450
AUDIENCE: Another question.

00:45:56.382 --> 00:45:59.606
You had an interesting example
of Bic and the pens, and how

00:45:59.606 --> 00:46:02.830
they redefined themselves from
a pen company to a disposable

00:46:02.830 --> 00:46:03.822
plastics company.

00:46:03.822 --> 00:46:07.790
And I'm wondering, have you
seen companies go through

00:46:07.790 --> 00:46:09.310
multiple iterations?

00:46:09.310 --> 00:46:13.718
So you redefine yourself
once, are they stuck

00:46:13.718 --> 00:46:15.710
with this new box?

00:46:15.710 --> 00:46:19.694
Have you seen companies go
through this multiple times?

00:46:19.694 --> 00:46:21.686
[INAUDIBLE]

00:46:21.686 --> 00:46:23.890
LUC DE BRABANDERE: Reuters
was a good example.

00:46:23.890 --> 00:46:25.430
Reuters.

00:46:25.430 --> 00:46:27.180
ALAN INY: Reuters is a good one
in the sense that, even

00:46:27.180 --> 00:46:29.540
though they kept their big
overarching box of we are

00:46:29.540 --> 00:46:33.010
this, they changed fundamentally
all of the

00:46:33.010 --> 00:46:35.520
underlying mechanics of
how they did that.

00:46:35.520 --> 00:46:38.280
So that's a good example
